    "However, traditional recommender systems grapple with the challenges posed by the immense volume, complexity, and dynamic nature of information (Zhang et al. 2020).",
    "The concept behind autoencoder-based recommender systems involves using AEs to acquire a lower-dimensional representation of both items and users.",
    "This representation can subsequently predict a user's preferences for items they haven't yet interacted with.",
    "Autoencoder-based recommender systems fall into two categories: pure autoencoder models and integrated autoencoder models, depending on the model architecture employed (Zhang et al. 2020).",
    "In pure autoencoder models, the autoencoder serves as the sole architecture for recommendation."
